@Randgalt The behavior changes for "/zoo/zoo/a" with a namespace "/zoo":

* Previously, the result is unfixed as "/a";
* Now, it's unfixed as "/zoo/a".

Previous tests do not cover this case, actually. A real-world case seldom use a prefix under the namespace with the same name.
